'3:38': [
{sup:1, word:"Adam", lines:["See {Mat1:1^1P4|note 1<sup>1</sup>, par. 4}, in {Mat1|Matt. 1}."]},
{sup:2, word:"son", lines:["This does not mean that Adam was born of God and possessed the life of God, just as son of Joseph does not mean that Jesus was born of Joseph; rather, He was thought to be the son of Joseph ({Luk3:23|v. 23}). Adam was created by God ({Gen5:1|Gen. 5:1}-{Gen5:2|2}), and God was his origin. Based on this he was considered the son of God, even as the heathen poets considered all mankind to be the offspring of God ({Act17:28|Acts 17:28}). Mankind was only created by God, not regenerated of Him. This is absolutely and intrinsically different from the believers in Christ being the sons of God. They have been born, regenerated, of God and possess God&rsquo;s life and nature ({Joh1:12|John 1:12}-{Joh1:13|13}; {Joh3:16|3:16}; {2Pe1:4|2&nbsp;Pet. 1:4})."]},
{sup:3, word:"God", lines:["From Jesus ({Luk3:23|v. 23}) back to God there are seventy-seven generations, in which are seen the history of God&rsquo;s creation, man&rsquo;s fall, God&rsquo;s promise, and man&rsquo;s salvation: of God, man was created ({Luk3:38|v. 38}; {Gen1:26|Gen. 1:26}-{Gen1:27|27}; {Gen2:7|2:7}); in Adam, man became fallen ({Luk3:38|v. 38}; {Gen3|Gen. 3}); through Abraham, man received God&rsquo;s promise ({Luk3:34|v. 34}; {Gen12:1|Gen. 12:1}-{Gen12:3|3}); and in Jesus, man is saved ({Luk3:23|v. 23}; {Luk2:10|2:10}-{Luk2:11|11})."]},
],
