'10:18': [
{sup:1, word:"fall", lines:["At the time of his rebellion against God, before the creation of man, Satan was judged and sentenced to be cast into Sheol (Hades), to the recesses (the deepest part) of the pit ({Isa14:15|Isa. 14:15}; {Ezk28:17|Ezek. 28:17}). Then God began to execute the sentence He had imposed on him. He has executed, and will execute, this sentence on different occasions and to different degrees, such as through the seventy disciples in this chapter, through Christ on the cross ({Heb2:14|Heb. 2:14}; {Joh12:31|John 12:31}), through the man-child and Michael before the great tribulation, when Satan will be cast down to the earth ({Rev12:5|Rev. 12:5}, {Rev12:7|7}-{Rev12:10|10}, {Rev12:13|13}), and through the angel before the millennium, when Satan will be cast into the abyss, the bottomless pit ({Rev20:1|Rev. 20:1}-{Rev20:3|3}). Finally, Satan will be cast into the lake of fire to suffer the punishment of eternal fire after the millennium ({Rev20:10|Rev. 20:10}) for eternity."]},
],
'10:19': [
{sup:"1a", word:"authority", vrefs:"Luke 9:1; Mark 3:15", lines:["What the Lord gave to the disciples was authority; what the enemy had was power. Authority subdues power."]},
{sup:"2b", word:"serpents", vrefs:"Psa. 91:13; Mark 16:18; Acts 28:3-5", lines:["Serpents may signify Satan and his angels ({Eph2:2|Eph. 2:2}; {Eph6:11|6:11}-{Eph6:12|12}); scorpions may signify the demons (vv. {Luk10:17|17}, {Luk10:20|20}). By the authority of the Lord the disciples subdued their evil power."]},
],
