'14:16': [
{sup:1, word:"great", lines:["This great dinner is different from the wedding feast in {Mat22:2|Matt. 22:2}-{Mat22:14|14}, which was for the reward of the kingdom. This great dinner is for God&rsquo;s full salvation. God, as the &ldquo;certain man,&rdquo; prepared His full salvation as a great dinner and sent the first apostles as His slaves to invite the Jews (vv. {Luk14:16|16}-{Luk14:17|17}). But because they were occupied by their riches, such as land, cattle, or a wife, they refused His invitation (vv. {Luk14:18|18}-{Luk14:20|20}). Then God sent the apostles to invite the people on the streets&mdash;the poor, the crippled, the blind, and the lame. Because of their poverty and misery, they accepted God&rsquo;s invitation (vv. {Luk14:21|21}-{Luk14:22|22a}). Yet God&rsquo;s salvation still had room for more; so He sent His slaves to go out farther, to the Gentile world, signified by the roads and hedges, to compel the Gentiles to come in and fill up the house of His salvation (vv. {Luk14:22|22b}-{Luk14:23|23}; {Act13:46|Acts 13:46}-{Act13:48|48}; {Rom11:25|Rom. 11:25})."]},
],
